Petrol attendant, Wiseman Ndabezitha filled a vehicle with petrol worth R210 only to have the driver tell him he wanted "two tens" worth. JOHANNESBURG - Don't you love it when someone tries to humiliate or bully someone else and it backfires? Well that's exactly what's happened. Petrol attendant, Wiseman Ndabezitha filled a vehicle with petrol worth R210 only to have the driver tell him he wanted "two tens" worth. READ: 'Keeping Up with the Kardashians' show to end in 2021 The customer paid R20 and drove off. But after a video of the exchange went viral on social media, South Africans started donating R210 each into Wiseman’s bank account. Now guess who's left with egg on their face?